# Document 01 — PRD

The north star. Write this before design, architecture, or code.

## Required sections

- App name and tagline
- Problem and who feels it
- Core value proposition
- Target user persona (2–3 sentences)
- Features: Must Have / Nice to Have
- User stories: `As a [user], I want to [action] so that [outcome]`
- Out of scope (explicit v1 exclusions)
- Success metrics

## Agent rules

- Derive TRD, App Flow, and Implementation Plan from the PRD — not the reverse.
- When asked to build a feature not in Must Have, ask if PRD should be updated first.
- Keep user stories testable; each maps to at least one App Flow journey.
